core

### Description

Currently if I want to create a debounced `rxResource` I need to do the following:
```ts
const email = signal('');

function isUnique(email: string) {
  return of(true).pipe(delay(300));
}

rxResource({
  params: email,
  stream: ({ params: email }) => timer(300).pipe(switchMap(() => isUnique(email))),
});
```
The `rxResource` stream function doesn't allow to react to changes in `params` over time reactively and requires here the usage of timer instead of `debounceTime`. 
Another limitation - there is always `switchMap` functionality which can be customized using the proposed solution

### Proposed solution

Allowing better control over `rxResource` using rxjs `pipe` function - so the above will be:
```ts
rxResource({
  params: email,
  stream: pipe(
    debounceTime(300),
    switchMap(({ params: email }) => isUnique(email)),
  ),
});
```

### Alternatives considered

Keep using the current method

